{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"peak-fir-hilt","description":"# Migrate the LLM gates onto the workflow engine\n\n## Context\n\nSecond of the two epics split out of soupy-spool-revel (6f2d) per the brainstorm (session logs\nboom-demon-jug ad3f + this design session). Depends on epic A (sage-votary-logic, 5766) which adds\nthe conditional-overlay and delegating-batch constructs the plan-review pipeline needs. Today the\nplan-review gate is a 707-LOC bespoke orchestrator (orchestrator.py, ThreadPoolExecutor fan-out)\nand verify_completion is a direct single-agent call (completion.py) — LLM gate logic lives OFF the\nunified engine substrate. This epic moves both onto the engine, validated by PLANNED-TRACE PARITY,\nand removes the throwaway sample workflows so only real workflows remain.\n\n## What\n\n- **Migrate plan-review onto the engine.** Re-express the 4-pass pipeline as an engine workflow:\n  overlay-resolved criterion-set -> `batch` finders -> aggregate `prompt` verify (ONE call) ->\n  `uses`/`branch` decide -> `prompt` coach; DET P1-P8 as a `uses` precheck. Supply the PRODUCTION\n  batch-runner by extracting the gate's sizing.py (adaptive batch + size-ladder + budget cap +\n  shed + fingerprint checkpoint) behind epic A's batch-runner seam.\n- **Migrate the completion verifier onto the engine.** It fits EXISTING concepts (no new\n  constructs): `uses`(deterministic child-closure+signature precheck) -> `prompt`(agentic, one\n  call) -> `uses`(reconcile/normalize) -> `uses`(sign). It is the simpler walking-skeleton migration.\n- **Planned-trace parity validation.** Run BOTH the bespoke and the workflow implementations in\n  parallel and assert PLANNED-TRACE parity — NOT result parity (the review is LLM-dependent and\n  variable). The planned trace is the ordered set of intended execution events:\n  [DET-check-id | (criterion/prompt-id, INTENDED model, call-mode agent|1-shot) | deterministic-step-id].\n  Parity is asserted on the PRE-ESCALATION planned trace, tolerating runtime size-ladder escalation\n  divergence. Run OFFLINE via the FakeRunner/FakeAgentRunner seam (no live calls) over a diverse\n  scenario corpus, so edge cases are tested exhaustively and cheaply (CI-able). Capture the\n  INTENDED/selected model (the fake echoes model=None), not the runner's echoed field.\n- **Remove the sample stubs.** Delete the throwaway example workflows (examples/code_review.yaml +\n  the templates.py scaffold per Joe's selection) once the migration lands; preserve forwarding\n  shims / public API for anything still referenced. KEEP epic A's demo workflow as the unused\n  visual-editing refinement sample.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Code-review migration (the real code-review reviewer is its own open epic; it will be updated\n  when these workflow changes land — not migrated here).\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- plan-review and completion-verification run on the ONE workflow-engine substrate (their prompts\n  in the engine prompt library), validated by offline planned-trace parity against the bespoke\n  implementations; only real workflows remain (samples removed).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] plan-review runs as an engine workflow (overlay-resolved criteria -> batch finders ->\n      aggregate verify -> decide -> coach; DET P1-P8 as a `uses` precheck), with the production\n      batch-runner extracted from sizing.py behind epic A's seam.\n- [ ] verify_completion runs as an engine workflow using existing step kinds only\n      (uses->prompt(agentic)->uses->uses); no new constructs needed.\n- [ ] A PLANNED-TRACE parity harness asserts the bespoke and workflow implementations issue the\n      same planned trace (same prompt-id + intended model + call-mode + deterministic steps),\n      pre-escalation, over a diverse OFFLINE scenario corpus (FakeRunner; no live calls); it runs in CI.\n- [ ] The bespoke orchestrator path is cut over to the workflow path behind the gate(s) once parity\n      holds; the close/claim gates keep working (signed verdicts/attestations intact).\n- [ ] The throwaway sample workflows (examples/code_review.yaml + templates.py scaffold) are removed\n      per Joe's selection; forwarding shims/public API preserved for anything still referenced;\n      epic A's demo workflow is retained as the visual-editing refinement sample.\n- [ ] End state: exactly two real LLM workflows (plan-review, completion-verification) + the one\n      retained sample; `make lint` + the full test suite pass.","id":"72d5-79ec-9e2e-4a2b","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"epic","title":"Migrate plan-review + completion-verification onto the workflow engine (planned-trace parity; remove sample stubs)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782371099945480001,"uuid":"b3762f12-e7b1-4c40-846b-e673bc44f2cd"}